Iavan Pijoos, News24(File, iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria &ndash; Police are investigating the death of an SA National Defence Force officer after his body was found at his home in Lyttelton, Pretoria, police said on Friday afternoon. Brigadier General Lindikhaya Mtirara, 51, was found lying on his bed with a gun wound to his upper body, police spokesperson Captain Mavela Masondo said. Family members alerted police after his body was found at 06:00 on Friday morning. Masondo said a firearm was found near Mtirara.&nbsp;Further information around the circumstances of his death was not immediately available.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.